question: Which signaling pathway does LY294002 inhibit?
ideal_answer: LY294002, can block the PI3K/AKT signaling pathway.

snippets.text: LY294002 Is a Promising Inhibitor to Overcome Sorafenib Resistance in FLT3-ITD Mutant AML Cells by Interfering With PI3K/Akt Signaling Pathway.
PI3K inhibitor, LY294002, can block PI3K/AKT signaling, further inhibit glycolysis to disturb ATP production, and finally induce cell apoptosis.
